liveBlogPostPrepared.title: HALF-TIME: Spain in control with a 3-0 lead over Costa Rica

liveBlogPostPrepared.plaintext: Spain were playing in the box. Fabiola Villalobos was penalised for bringing down Spain's Olga Carmona in the penalty area. Truth be told, they didn't touch each other. Carmona could be up for a Logie with that performance. But Costa Rica's goalkeeper was up to the task, parrying away Jenni Hermoso's attempt.

liveBlogPostPrepared.plaintext: Spain are on fire. They peppered the penalty box. Corners and saves. Then finally the third goal comes. The cross was fired in from the left. Number 10 Jenni Hermoso headers it into the crossbar. It bounces back and Esther González finishes it off.
